io.github.utk003.util.misc.annotations

Annotation Type PlannedFeature


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value={TYPE,METHOD,FIELD,CONSTRUCTOR,PACKAGE})
 @ScheduledForRelease(inVersion="v3.0.0")
 @Repeatable(value=PlannedFeatures.class)
public @interface PlannedFeature
    Indicates that the given class, method, field, etc. will be modified in the future to accommodate new features.

    Any item marked by this annotation is has upcoming features, each described in its own @PlannedFeature annotation. This annotation can specify planned version of release, if known.

    Example usages include: 

     @PlannedFeature("public static void main(String[] args)")
 @PlannedFeature(
     value = "protected void dolorSit(int amet)",
     description = "Do <some action>",
     version = "v0.0.0"
 )
 public class LoremIpsum {
 }

    Multiple @PlannedFeature annotations can be applied to a single definition, as shown in the example above.

    Since:
    3.0.0
    Version:
    July 20, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)
